Vistual Studio 2022 Community Edition <ol> <li>You can use Visual Studio 2019 edition or further editions.</li> <li>You can download and set up using the guide.  </li> </ol> Aneka SDK <ol> <li>Aneka SDK can copied from the location where Aneka is installed. For example <code>C:\Program Files (x86)\Manjrasoft\Aneka.5.0\Tools\SDK</code></li> <li>Thread, Comman and Runtime libraries are required to create a thread application.</li> </ol> Ankea configuration file <code>conf.xml</code> <ol> <li>Change the <code>SchedulerUri</code> value of IP address to your Master IP address.</li> <li>Change username and password to Master machine credentials.</li> <li>You can save the <code>conf.xml</code> in convenient location in developer machine.</li> </ol> <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?&gt;
  &lt;Aneka&gt;
    &lt;UseFileTransfer value="true" /&gt;
    &lt;Workspace value="." /&gt;
    &lt;SingleSubmission value="false" /&gt;
    &lt;ResubmitMode value="AUTO" /&gt;
    &lt;PollingTime value="1000" /&gt;
    &lt;LogMessages value="true" /&gt;
    &lt;SchedulerUri value="tcp://44.201.249.32:9090/Aneka" /&gt;
    &lt;UserCredential type="Aneka.Security.UserCredentials" assembly="Aneka"&gt;
      &lt;Instance username="admin" password="123456"/&gt;
    &lt;/UserCredential&gt;
  &lt;/Aneka&gt;
</code></pre>
